Package: anchormap
Title: Competitive, Size- and Correlation-Aware Cluster Anchoring
Version: 0.1.3
Authors@R:
    person("Michael", "Preuss", email = "preuss_micha@icloud.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Given latent cluster factors and their genetic correlations
    (rg) to a trait panel, AnchorMap scores - competitively, size-aware,
    and correlation-aware - which ontology domain each cluster anchors to,
    how confidently, and whether the anchor is sharp or diffuse. It ingests
    either a standardized rg long-table (plus an optional trait x trait rg
    matrix) or a GenomicSEM ldsc() .rds artifact directly, runs a parallel
    reliability-threshold sensitivity sweep, and renders publication-ready
    figures. The engine is exposed both as a library (run_anchormap(),
    run_plots(), run_sensitivity()) and as command-line entry points.
